# Changelog Updates

When making user-facing changes to dashboard files, update the changelog in `dashboard/index.html`.

## Location

The changelog lives inside `<div class="changelog-modal">` near the bottom of `index.html`. Entries are ordered newest-first.

## Format

Each entry follows this pattern:

```html
<div class="cl-entry">
    <div class="cl-version">vX.Y <span class="cl-date">Mon DD, YYYY</span> <span class="cl-tag TYPE">Label</span></div>
    <ul>
        <li>Change description</li>
    </ul>
</div>
```

Tag types: `feature`, `fix`, `improvement`

## Rules

- Bump the minor version (e.g. v2.3 -> v2.4) for each batch of changes
- Use today's date
- Add the new entry as the FIRST `cl-entry` inside the modal (above existing entries)
- Keep descriptions concise (one line per change)
- Only log user-visible or operationally significant changes -- skip pure refactors unless they affect behavior
